						               													<description>Triplexity ... a game of complex simplicity, otherwise known as vertical tic-tac-toe.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal: to be the first to place your 3 colour pieces in a single stack or on the top of each of 3 stacks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take turns placing their pieces, one at a time, in 3 positions: left, centre, right - stack max. 3 pieces high.&amp;#10;When all 6 pieces have been placed, the game continues with players moving any colour piece &amp;ndash; yes, even the opponent's.&amp;#10;The piece last moved may not be returned to its previous position on the next turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Triplexity (Advanced) is played, in the same way, for points.&amp;#10;Play an agreed number of rounds or to a target score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The pieces, numbered with pips similar to opposite sides of a regular die, are placed either-way-up and are always inverted when moved.&amp;#10;Tally the number of pips face-up on the 3 winning pieces to determine the score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;FYI &amp;ndash; the pieces are a pair of thrice-sliced dice and the game can be brain-bending (mind-numbing)!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
